    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About ALSO.\n\nWe’re ALSO, an electric mobility company originally conceived as a part of Rivian. We’re a passionate team of builders, dreamers, doers and innovators, focused on creating entirely new (not to mention, innovative and delightful) vertically integrated, small EVs designed to meet the global mobility challenges of today and tomorrow. Our mission is to inspire everyone to ride ALSO—replacing many local car, truck and SUV miles with ones on vehicles that are more affordable, more enjoyable and 10-50x more efficient.\n\nALSO is looking for a Sr. Staff Systems Engineer to play a key role in defining and supporting requirements development and feature development on various electric mobility vehicles!\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n - Drive architecture and requirements development for a cross-functional micromobility vehicle platform program (Electrical Engineering, Firmware, Product Design) from a systems engineering perspective, ensuring alignment from concept through validation.\n\n - Serve as the primary technical interface between customers and ALSO leadership to capture product intent and translate it into clear system artifacts including user stories, CONOPS, and use cases.\n\n - Define and manage requirements at the system, subsystem, and hardware module levels in close collaboration with internal stakeholders across:\n   \n   - Low-voltage electronics\n   \n   - Battery and energy storage systems\n   \n   - Drivetrain and actuators\n   \n   - Connectivity and telematics\n   \n   - Human–Machine Interfaces (HMI)\n   \n   - Sensor systems\n\n - Ensure end-to-end traceability across user stories, features, system requirements, subsystem requirements, and verification/validation test cases.\n\n - Develop and maintain system architectures for distributed embedded controllers, including:\n   \n   - Interface definitions and communication protocols\n   \n   - Functional decomposition and allocation\n   \n   - Fault detection, fault handling, and system-level robustness\n\n - Collaborate closely with software engineers, electrical engineers, product designers, product managers, and UI/UX teams to drive CONOPS, activity diagrams, feature design, development, and validation.\n\n - Develop state machines such as for power states for the platform\n\n - Support end-to-end feature validation, contributing to the definition and execution of test cases and test plans across:\n   \n   - Bench and HIL testing\n   \n   - Vehicle-level bring-up\n   \n   - System integration and performance validation\n\nWhat You Will Bring\n\n - BS/MS in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science or related field\n\n - 8+ years of professional experience in systems engineering or embedded software development\n\n - Understanding of Real Time Operating Systems (RTOS)\n\n - Experience working with embedded systems\n\n - Extensive knowledge of automotive communication protocols (CAN, CAN FD, SPI)\n\n - Requirements management tools such as JAMA, or Polarion and using model based systems engineering\n\n\nThe salary for this position ranges from $200,000-$250,000 per year, depending on experience and qualifications.\n\nWhy ALSO.\n\nWe’re passionate about helping the world find a better way to get there—wherever it is you’re headed.\n\nWe’re located in the heart of Silicon Valley and have brought together a world-class team from some of the biggest brands in the technology, automotive, cycling, outdoor recreation and retail spaces. \n\nTogether we’re working hands-on to imagine, design and build an entirely new solution to a global set of transportation challenges. \n\nPerks and Benefits\n\n - Robust health coverage. Excellent health, dental and vision insurance covered up to 100% by ALSO with FSA \u0026 HSA options.\n\n - One Medical membership and dedicated insurance advocates.\n\n - Rich fertility and family building benefits with Progyny.\n\n - Flexible time off. \n\n - 401(k) match.",
